00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.000
How to fold Kimono/Yukata by Keiko Tsuda, Kimono Lifestyle Consultant

00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.000
Put your kimono collar in your left side.

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:18.000
You don't have to move at all. 

00:00:22.000 --> 00:00:30.000
Fold upward at the right sewing line.

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:36.000
Concentrate on your bottom part of Kimono.

00:00:39.000 --> 00:00:45.000
Put left side of kimono onto the right side as you folded.

00:00:53.000 --> 00:00:59.000
Confirm your sewing line of back goes straight.

00:00:59.000 --> 00:01:05.000
Fold up the bottom to upward and pull down upper part of Kimono/Yukata to your front.

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:18.000
The same as you did before at the bottom part.

00:01:27.000 --> 00:01:33.000
Watch carefully,(you should make triangle shape) at the back of collar.

00:01:46.000 --> 00:01:49.000
Fold each sleeves (upward &amp; downward).

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:06.000
Fold in two parts.

00:02:09.000 --> 00:02:18.000
Fold in three parts. Be careful! No wrinkles at the sleeves.

00:02:22.000 --> 00:02:31.000
You will learn how to fold Kimono/Yukata for men and women
